reviews.text:
l like this place, little bit crowded every Weekend.
Fast service, friendly staff even they are so busy.
Tasty food and in right quantity. Budget place.

for the price of the food, don't expect too much.
flavours are decent, the style of service is fine for how they operate.
but one thing that does let me down is how the staff dress, their uniform seem a bit dirty.
Reasonable price and efficient delivery of food. Worth a try.

OK Italian food at very reasonable prices. Portions are not too big, which we find a big plus. Free refills for sodas and iced teas. Seems popular, with some waiting needed to get a table. Service is quite fast.

Surely one cannot expect too much from a restaurant offering snack-like dishes ranging from 15 to 30 HKD，and one can drink as much soft drinks, coffee or tea as you like by paying $13 more. 
Food is pre-made in bulk supposedly but dishes come with an above average standard. If you go in a small group of four, you can have a full meal at around HKD200, having a large variety of small dishes.
Don't go at school break hours as kids take it as their canteen.
